General Information

Unichi Bird's Nest in Capsules contain a concentrated powder of high quality Edible Bird's Nest which is known in the scientific community as "Cubilose". Edible Bird's Nest is a delicacy found in traditional Asian cuisine and culture, often consumed by women before and during pregnancy. Unichi Bird's Nest in Capsules is rich in sialic acid which is only found in authentic Edible Bird's Nest powder. Sialic acid is an essential component found in all cells of the body and is especically common in the brain and skin.

Warnings

Store below 30 in a dry place, away from direct sunlight. Do not use if blister seal is broken.

Common Uses

The consumption of Edible Bird's Nest has been a tradition for many centuries in China with one of the most well-known historical users being Yang Gui Fei, who was one of the Four Beauties of Ancient China. Historical records indicate that Yang Gui Fei would consume Edible Bird's Nest regularly as a routine in maintaining her beauty and youthful looks. Edible Bird's Nest sourced from caves is high in sialic acid. Sialic acid is found everywhere in the human body and performs numerous biological functions, particularly in the brain and central nervous system.

Ingredients

Microcrystalline Cellulose, Hypromellose, Edible Bird's Nest (Cubilose) powder, Ascorbic Acid, Silica, Magnesium Stearate, Iron Oxide Hydrated.

No added lactose, gluten, yeast, egg or artifical flavours.

Directions

Consume 2 capsules daily with meals. Capsule may be separated and contents sprinkled onto food.
